          "text": "Perfect! I've created a minimal shader pipeline with three nodes:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Nodes created:**\n1. **Simple Red Shader** (Shader node) — Contains basic GLSL that outputs solid red (`vec4(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0)`)\n2. **Red Material** (Material node) — Combines the shader with texture/normal inputs\n3. **Colored Quad** (Sprite node) — A 100×100 quad positioned at (200, 150) that uses the red material\n\n**Wiring:**\n- Shader output → Material's shader input\n- Material output → Sprite's material input\n\nThe sprite will render as a solid red square. This demonstrates the complete shader pipeline: shader code → material composition → sprite rendering.\n\nYou can easily modify the shader code in the \"Simple Red Shader\" node to create more complex effects (gradients, waves, etc.) by updating the shader's `code` data field."
